                  <persName id="t18310630-226-person1698">
                  JOHN 
                  AXTILL
               <interp inst="t18310630-226-person1698" type="surname" value="AXTILL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-226-person1698" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310630-226-person1698" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18310630-226-viclabel1190" type="occupation">milkman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310630-226-victim1697 t18310630-226-viclabel1190"></join>, and live in Cromer-<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183106300111"></xptr>street. The prisoner is my son, and has been to sea - he was at home with me for about a fortnight; I missed a sovereign and nine shillings out of the till in my parlour, about eight o'clock on Sunday evening - he had been in the parlour, and immediately he went out I went to the till, suspecting him, and missed the money; he did not return - I found him at a public-house by the London-docks, at twelve o'clock at night, and found 3s. 9d. on him; he said he had robbed me; nobody else could have taken it - I had seen it in the till that afternoon.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. My father drove me out of doors.</p>
               <p>JOHN AXTILL. It is not true - he is constantly leaving home; I have five children at home.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310630-226-verdict1191" type="verdictDescription">
